tfse
  • Reference

SEM fit statistics

Returns data frame of SEM fit statistics

SEM parameter table

sem_fit(x, digits = 3, scaled = TRUE)

par_table(x)

Arguments

x

Object of class lavaan.
digits

Number of digits to round to, Defaults to 3.
scaled

Logical indicating whether to return scaled fit indices if available.
x

Object of class lavaan

Value

Fit statistics tibble.

Tibble of parameter estimates

Examples

## specify model
m1 <- 'e =~ cyl + hp + wt\nmpg ~ e + gear'

## function to normalize data
normalize <- function(x) (x - mean(x, na.rm = TRUE)) / sd(x, na.rm = TRUE)

## fit model
f1 <- lavaan::sem(
  m1,
  data = tibble::as_tibble(dplyr::mutate_if(mtcars, is.numeric, normalize)),
  std.lv = TRUE,
  estimator = "mlr"
)

## view fit stats
sem_fit(f1)
#> Scaled fit statistics
#> # A tibble: 1 x 7
#>       N ChiSq   CFI   TLI RMSEA      RMSEA_ci  SRMR

#> 1     5 40.88 0.735  0.47 0.474 [0.341,0.619] 0.198
